com.joliciel.talismane.lexicon

Interface LexicalEntry

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    WritableLexicalEntry
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CompactLexicalEntry

    public interface LexicalEntry
extends java.io.Serializable
    A single lexical entry for a given string.
    Author:
    Assaf Urieli

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.util.List<java.lang.String> getAspect()
      A list of possible (language-specific) aspects for this entry, when the entry is a verb.
      java.lang.String getAttribute(java.lang.String attribute)
      Get any attribute for this lexical entry, as a String.
      If the attribute is a LexicalAttribute, it will return the corresponding attribute.
      If it is a String, will try to match it to an existing OtherAttribute, and return the corresponding value.
      If the attribute is a List, the items will be joined together into a single pipe-delimited String.
      java.util.List<java.lang.String> getAttributeAsList(java.lang.String attribute)
      Like getAttribute(String), but if the original attribute is a String, will convert it to a List of length 1.

        java.lang.String getMorphology()
